events.info: Discover why no dream is too big at Disney On Ice presents Into the Magic! Seek adventure in the great wide somewhere with Belle as she explores the Beasts enchanted castle, experience Moanas courage to embark on a voyage with demigod Maui to save her island, and sing-along with Miguel from Coco as he follows the music in his heart. Be inspired by Annas devotion to her sister Elsa on her journey to the North Mountain to stop the eternal winter, and watch Rapunzel and Flynn go to great lengths to make her dream come true. Celebrate the magic of courage, love and adventure at Disney On Ice! *Note: Costumes not permitted for guests 14 years & older. Visit DisneyOnIce.com for more information.
events.pleaseNote: - All guests age 2 & older are required to have a ticket. - No costumes for guests 14 & older. - Please monitor the venue website for venue policies, including health and safety protocols, which are subject to change. - All tickets are subject to availability. - Prices are subject to change. - Visit DisneyOnIce.com for more info.

Be inspired by Annas devotion to her sister Elsa on her journey to the North Mountain to stop the eternal winter, and watch Rapunzel and Flynn go to great lengths to make her dream come true. Celebrate the magic of courage, love and adventure at Disney On Ice! *Note: Costumes not permitted for guests 14 years & older. Visit DisneyOnIce.com for more information.
events.pleaseNote: All guests age 2 & older are required to have a ticket. No costumes for guests 14 & older. Please monitor the venue website for venue policies, including health and safety protocols, which are subject to change. All tickets are subject to availability. Prices are subject to change. Visit DisneyOnIce.com for more info.

venues.name: XL CENTER

boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: Monday - Friday 12 - 4 pm
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: Mastercard, Visa, AMEX, Discover, Cash
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: NOTE: The XL Center does not allow alternate pick up names for will call. Guests who have ordered tickets via phone/internet will need to present proper photo ID and the credit card used to charge the tickets. Both must be under the same name. Customers may pick up their tickets anytime the box office is open the day of the event. Customers must present the actual credit card used to place the order and two forms of ID, including a photo ID.

venues.parkingDetail: Parking is available surrounding the XL Center and throughout downtown Hartford. There are 45 parking lots and garages in downtown Hartford. Prices for the garages and parking lots may vary and are run through third-party companies. For questions regarding the respective parking garages or lots, please reach out to those organizations directly.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: The XL Center is committed to providing all patrons the opportunity to enjoy our events. For this reason, the XL Center and its staff make it a priority to accommodate the needs of individuals with disabilities and their companions. Mobility device, wheelchair, and limited mobility seating is available. For more info, visit the ADA Information page on our website.

generalInfo.generalRule: The XL Center has a no re-entry policy. Guests are not allowed to smoke in the XL Center. Cameras with detachable lenses, outside food and beverage, weapons, backpacks, and more are not allowed. Please visit the FAQ page on our website for the full list of prohibited items.
generalInfo.childRule: Children 2+ require a ticket.

ada.adaCustomCopy: Accessible seating is available on online to purchase.
ada.adaHours:
Box office is open Monday - Friday 12-4 pm
    
NOTE: The Box Office will remain open evenings when an event is scheduled until 1 hour after the beginning of the event.  If a weekend event is scheduled, the Box Office will open at least 4 hours prior to the event    
start time.

events.name: Boston Bruins vs. Edmonton Oilers
events.pleaseNote: Guests attending TD Garden events are advised that laptops, bags, backpacks, luggage, coolers, parcels, briefcases and like articles will be strictly prohibited from the facility. All guests may be subject to search of their person and/or possessions. Patrons with prohibited articles will be turned away and no storage or "check-in area" will be provided. Enforcement will be without exceptions.

products.name: TD Garden Event Parking North Station Garage - Bruins v. Oilers

ticketLimit.info: There is an overall 8 ticket limit for this event.

venues.name: TD Garden

boxOfficeInfo.phoneNumberDetail: General Info Number:(617) 624-1000 Group Sales (only!): (617) 624-1805/1806 Bruins (617) 624-BEAR (Groups = 25+) Celtics (617) 523-3030 (Groups = 20+) Please do not contact Group Sales regarding sold out games!
boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: TD Garden - Boston | Tickets, Schedule, Seating Chart, Directions (ticketmaster.com) The box office will open 2 hours prior to an event and remain open until one hour after the event begins. Please note the TD Garden Box Office does not sell tickets at the public on sale. All tickets should be purchased via www.ticketmaster.com *Hours subject to change
boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: Cash; Check up to $100.00 w/Mass. Driver License; AMEX; Visa; MC; Discover; Diners Club
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Pick up tickets starting 2 hours prior to event time. Customer must present the actual credit card used to place order and a photo I.D.

venues.parkingDetail: Park under The TD Garden in the new garage or in one of the several lots around the building.

generalInfo.generalRule: Alcohol Policy : To purchase alcoholic beverages, a patron must present a valid MA driver's license, MA liquor ID, passport or military ID, which indicates the patron to be a least 21 years of age (MA ID cards, duplicate licenses, expired licenses, damaged licenses and driver's licenses, which do not have photos, will not be accepted). Out of state licenses are acceptable only if the patron is at least 25 years of age and another form of identification (e.g., credit card) will be required if the patron is between 25 and 30 years of age. For out of country patrons, only a valid Passport will be accepted as proof of identification. No smoking is allowed in the building.
generalInfo.childRule: Children under 2 free on adults lap for all events, Celtics, Bruins, family shows, and concerts. Some exceptions may apply.
